2. If `y₀` is not reversible in `x` (i.e., `¬ Reversible x y₀ p`), then `reverseSet x y₀ p = {y₀}`. But this leads to a contradiction because `unreverse y₀` would be in `{y₀}`, implying `unreverse y₀ = y₀`, which contradicts the fact that `y₀` is not reversible in `x`.

In both cases, we arrive at a contradiction, proving that `¬ Reversible (x.unreverse) y p`.

